## Usage
Archives the frontmost browser tab using Internet Archive's Wayback Machine. Alternatively, you can pass in a URL as an argument, or perform the action from Alfred clipboard history with the Universal Action.
- <kbd>︎</kbd> Archive and copy the archive URL to clipboard. - <kbd></kbd><kbd>︎</kbd> Skip the check for existing snapshots. Directly request to create a new one. - <kbd></kbd><kbd>︎</kbd> Copy the resulting URL in markdown format: `[archive](<URL>)` - <kbd></kbd><kbd>︎</kbd> Open the Wayback Machine website for archiving. No automatic copy to clipboard.
## Settings
- **Keyword** - Set this to whatever is most convenient for you - **Snapshot Tolerance** - This determines how old an existing snapshot has to be for the workflow to create a new snaptshot - **Maximum Wait for Requests** - Stops the workflow from getting stuck while waiting for a response - **Always On Logging?** - Turn on logs in the workflow data folder
## Feedback
Please provide feedback in [the dedicated topic on the Alfred "Share Your Workflows" forum](https://www.alfredforum.com/forum/3-share-your-workflows/).
The number of days to use as a tolerance range for creating new snapshots. If an existing snapshot is within this range, then a new snapshot is not created.
How long (in seconds) to wait for requests (to Internet Archive) to resolve. Note that this is per request, not the total wait time across the whole workflow.
Enable this option to log key information to the workflow data folder. This is useful if you need to debug problems with the workflow. The logs are cleared periodically.
